-- Bank of America $590 Million Lehman Payment Order ‘Not Final’
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2010-12-30T14:25:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-30/bank-of-america-590-million-lehman-brothers-payment-order-is-not-final-.html
A bankruptcy judge amended his order
that Bank of America Corp. pay Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.
$590 million in compensation for taking its deposits, saying
“the judgment is hereby deemed not to be a final judgment,”
according to a filing yesterday in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in
Manhattan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
